69th Legislature 2025 HB 496.1
1 HOUSE BILL NO. 496
2 INTRODUCED BY E. BUTTREY, S. FITZPATRICK, B. BARKER, B. MERCER, K. SULLIVAN
3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT AMENDING LAWS RELATED TO THE RETROCESSION OF
5 JURISDICTION OVER FEDERAL LANDS; PROVIDING FOR ACCEPTANCE OF JURISDICTION OVER
6 FEDERAL LANDS USED FOR MILITARY PURPOSES; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 2-1-215 AND 2-1-216,
7 MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 2-1-215, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "2-1-215. Acceptance of jurisdiction over federal lands. The consent of the state is hereby given
13 to the retrocession of jurisdiction, either partially or wholly, by the United States of America over lands owned
14 by the United States of America within the boundaries of Montana that are used for national park or military
15 purposes. The governor is authorized to accept for the state retrocession of jurisdiction."
16
17 Section 2. Section 2-1-216, MCA, is amended to read:
18 "2-1-216. Filing of acceptance of jurisdiction over federal lands. (1) When the state receives
19 written notification from the authorized official or agent of the United States of America that the United States
20 desires or is willing to relinquish to the state jurisdiction, or a portion thereof of jurisdiction, over certain lands
21 owned by the United States within Montana that are used for national park or military purposes, the governor
22 may accept relinquishment.
23 (2) After acceptance and approval by the governor, retrocession of jurisdiction becomes effective
24 upon on filing of the original acceptance with the secretary of state of Montana."
25 - END -
